---

<main class="main-content">
  <section class="content-container">

    <section class="section-block">
      <h1 class="section-heading">TGK Community</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        A gathering place for readers, seekers, contrarians, and builders of The Gnostic Key.
        Here, arguments are sharpened, assumptions tested, and interpretations refined through
        disciplined, respectful dialogue.
      </p>

      <!-- ✦ Charter Link -->
      <p class="muted small">
        For full principles and expectations, read the 
        <a href="/pillars/tgk-community/charter/" class="link-accent">
          TGK Community Charter
        </a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ✦ Removed detailed ethos + rules block that was previously here -->

    <section class="section-block">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Community Gateways</h2>

    <div class="community-grid portal-grid">
      {% for m in communityGrid %}

        {% set state = m.state or "default" %}

        <article class="gnostic-card {{ state }}">
          <a class="card-link" href="{{ m.href }}">

            <div class="card-body">
              {% if m.glyph %}
                <div class="card-glyph">{{ m.glyph }}</div>
              {% endif %}
              <h3 class="card-title">{{ m.title }}</h3>
              {% if m.desc %}
                <p class="card-desc">{{ m.desc }}</p>
              {% endif %}
            </div>

            {% if state == "coming-soon" %}
              <div class="card-overlay"><span class="banner">Coming Soon</span></div>
            {% endif %}

            <div class="card-badge tier-free">Free</div>
          </a>
        </article>

      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>

    <section class="section-block">
      <h2 class="section-heading">The Steel Man Principle</h2>
      <p>
        Every reply begins with a discipline: 
        <strong>summarise the argument you are addressing, in your own words.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        This is the signature ethic that defines the TGK Community.
        It protects clarity, prevents distortion, and makes disagreement productive.
      </p>
      <p class="muted small">
        The full version of this principle is outlined in the
        <a href="/pillars/tgk-community/charter/" class="link-accent">Community Charter</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

  </section>
</main>
